## Summary

The first part talks about my family migration story and how migration shaped my family history and identity. Before learning more, I thought my family background was simply Italian and Chinese, but I later realised that many generations of my family moved between places because of work, opportunities, family connections, and the hope for a better future. I also reflected on the cultural differences between Taiwan and Italy, including transportation, language, food, and lifestyle. These differences showed me how migration can completely change the way people live.

The second part is written from the perspective of an Indonesian worker living in Taiwan and working for TSMC. The worker sacrifices time with his family in order to earn money and provide better educational opportunities for his children. He describes Taiwan as convenient and affordable while also expressing homesickness and concern for his family’s future. The letter highlights themes of sacrifice, migration, education, and the desire to improve the next generation’s life.
